newsitem.title: USA: INSIGHT--Dlr to zigzag up in "top-building" move.
newsitem.headline: INSIGHT--Dlr to zigzag up in "top-building" move.

text.p: The dollar is seen ratcheting higher over the next few days as it gradually makes its way above resistance at 110.40 yen and 1.5165/75 marks, technical analysts said.
Breaks above those levels would set the stage for further extensions to 1.5200 marks and eventually to 111.20 in dollar/yen, the said.

"I see dollar/mark in the process of top-building. Maybe we'll work our way as high as 1.52 (marks) over the next few days. But again, it's very rangy top building," said David Solin, technicals partner at Foreign Exchange Analytics.
